@gwenshap I'm still working out the last bits of the DistributedHerderTest, need to wait for KAFKA-2464 to land, and need to check if I broke the distributed copycat system test, but this is mostly complete and there's more than enough here to look at.

Note that there are a few items that we need REST API support for because they require some requests between brokers. I've marked those as FIXME or TODO with notes about why we need the REST API first.

Since the REST API isn't there yet, to do real testing of the deleteConnector API, I had to manually add/remove `herder.deleteConnector(name)` calls to `main()`. I didn't want to spend time on making the command line more flexible since it's just going to be removed anyway.

